The paper deals with the challenge of self-organization of a large sensor network, which involves developing algorithms and protocols for the swarm to organize itself into large-scale structures. This falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and protocols, which are related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DS) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of global routing, tracking, and guiding algorithms, which are related to Robotics (cs.RO).
